abstract: SPRINGFIELD, Mass., March 9. -- The Albion Paper Company of Holyoke is unable to meet obligations, and a meeting of creditors is called for Saturday afternoon. The failure was unexpected. All notes at the bank have been met up to to-day. No attachments are recorded, but the officers say that there is no prospect of relief. The debts are said to amount to over $500,000, some placing them at $700,000.
